    "body": "Adding the data URL of image to `context-menu` is not an option, it would add the overhead of encoding image and sending the image through IPC for every right click.\n\nTo implement a copy image menu, the simplest way is to add a `webContents.copyImageAt` API, which is the way used by Chromium.\n\nRefs:\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/content/public/browser/render_frame_host.h?sq=package:chromium&l=175\n"
